         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that the Kronrod extension to the $n$-point Gauss integration rule, with respect to the weight function $(1 - x^2)^{\mu-1/2}, 0 &lt; \mu \leqslant 2, \mu \neq 1$, is of exact precision $3n + 1$ for $n$ even and $3n + 2$ for $n$ odd. Similarly, for the $(n + 1)$-point Lobatto rule, with $-1/2 &lt; \mu \leqslant 1, \mu \neq 0$, the exact precision is $3n$ for $n$ odd and $3n + 1$ for $n$ even.</p>
          </abstract>
